<li><a href="https://www.gtk.org/">GTK</a> - The de facto library for GUI development in Vala. Bindings are included with the vala compiler.</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2021-26</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2021-26</guid><pubDate>Mon, 28 Jun 2021 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[desiderantes/awesome-vala Nov 9th - Nov 15th, 2020]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>Graphic Libraries</h2>
<li><a href="https://www.libsdl.org/">SDL2</a> - A cross-platform development library designed to provide low level access to audio, keyboard, mouse, joystick, and graphics hardware via OpenGL, Direct3D, and Vulkan. Bindings are included in Vala and will be available starting with Vala 0.52.</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-46</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-46</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Nov 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[desiderantes/awesome-vala Oct 5th - Oct 11th, 2020]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>Numerical Computation</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/fusilero/libbalistica">balistica</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/fusilero/libbalistica" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">4</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":4,"repo":"fusilero/libbalistica"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An open source ballistic simulation library. There's a complete calculator <a href="https://github.com/fusilero/balistica">here</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/fusilero/balistica" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">33</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":33,"repo":"fusilero/balistica"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>
<h2>Data Structures &#x26; Data Types</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/lcallarec/united">United</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/lcallarec/united" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">5</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":5,"repo":"lcallarec/united"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A library for unit manipulation (like kilograms, meters, etc).</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-41</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-41</guid><pubDate>Mon, 05 Oct 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[desiderantes/awesome-vala Sep 28th - Oct 4th, 2020]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>IoC and Dependency Injection</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/nahuelwexd/Vadi">Vadi</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/nahuelwexd/Vadi" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">12</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":12,"repo":"nahuelwexd/Vadi"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An IoC Container developed in order to facilitate the usage of dependency injection for Vala developers.</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-40</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-40</guid><pubDate>Mon, 28 Sep 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[desiderantes/awesome-vala Jan 27th - Feb 2nd, 2020]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>Language Servers</h2>
<li><a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/esodan/gvls">GVLS</a> - A service that provides code completion and formatting for Vala. This does not currently work with Visual Studio Code due to missing details on the lsp implementation, but it does work with GNOME Builder.</li>
<h2>Numerical Computation</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/rainwoodman/vast">vast</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/rainwoodman/vast" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">9</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":9,"repo":"rainwoodman/vast"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A project for generative modeling in Vala. Think of TensorFlow rewritten in Vala.</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-5</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2020-5</guid><pubDate>Mon, 27 Jan 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[desiderantes/awesome-vala Oct 14th - Oct 20th, 2019]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>Language Servers</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/benwaffle/vala-language-server">vala-language-server</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/benwaffle/vala-language-server" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">170</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":170,"repo":"benwaffle/vala-language-server"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A language server that aims to provide code completion, formatting, syntax highlighting, and everything else according to the Language Server spec.</li>
<h2>Editor Plugins</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/thiagoabreu/vala-code">Vala Code</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/thiagoabreu/vala-code" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">34</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":34,"repo":"thiagoabreu/vala-code"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A plugin for VIsual Studio Code that enables basic autocompletion and syntax highlighting for Vala.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/technosophos/Vala-TMBundle">Vala-TMBundle</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/technosophos/Vala-TMBundle" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">21</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":21,"repo":"technosophos/Vala-TMBundle"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A TextMate bundle that provides Vala syntax highlighting, code completion, etc. Sublime Text 3 can also use this plugin.</li>
<li><a href="https://atom.io/packages/language-vala-modern">language-vala-modern</a> - Provides Vala language support in Atom. It's a fork of the unmaintained "language-vala package".</li>
<li><a href="https://launchpad.net/valasyntax4sublimetext">Vala Syntax 4 Sublime Text</a> - A basic plugin for Sublime Text 3 that provides syntax highlighting.</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2019-42</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2019-42</guid><pubDate>Mon, 14 Oct 2019 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[desiderantes/awesome-vala Nov 26th - Dec 2nd, 2018]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>XML &#x26; Data Serialization</h2>
<li><a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gxml/">GXML</a> - A GObject API for manipulating XML and a Serializable framework from GObject to XML.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/rainwoodman/libyaml-glib">libyaml-glib</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/rainwoodman/libyaml-glib" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":11,"repo":"rainwoodman/libyaml-glib"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The GLib binding of libyaml, plus a GObject builder that understands YAML.</li>
<li><a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/json-glib/">Json-GLib</a> - Implements a full JSON parser and generator using GLib and GObject, and integrates JSON with GLib data types.</li>
<h2>Data Structures &#x26; Data Types</h2>
<li><a href="https://wiki.gnome.org/Projects/Libgee">Libgee</a> - A utility library providing GObject-based interfaces and classes for commonly used data structures (lists, maps, queues, trees, etc.).</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/ebassi/graphene">Graphene</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/ebassi/graphene" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">274</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":274,"repo":"ebassi/graphene"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A thin layer of types for graphic libraries. It provides common types needed to handle 3D transformations: points, triangles, rectangles, quads, quaternions, vectors, matrices, spheres, etc.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/arteymix/numeric-glib">Numeric-GLib</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/arteymix/numeric-glib" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">8</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":8,"repo":"arteymix/numeric-glib"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A collection of numeric data types for GLib (and Vala) via GCC extensions. It includes 128 bit integers &#x26; floats, complex types, vectorized operations, and decimal types.</li>
<h2>Graphic Libraries</h2>
<li><a href="https://cairographics.org/">Cairo</a> - A 2D graphics library with support for multiple output devices. This is pretty much the default library you get in Vala.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/ev3dev/grx">GRX</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/ev3dev/grx" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">12</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":12,"repo":"ev3dev/grx"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A graphics library for simple graphics displays (think 1-bit displays or Adafruit's PiTFT displays). It also includes keyboard, mouse, joystick and touchscreen input support.</li>
<li><a href="http://gegl.org/">GEGL</a> - A data flow based image processing framework, providing floating point processing and non-destructive image processing capabilities. Think of it as "Reactive Programming for Images".</li>
<li><a href="http://gegl.org/babl/">Babl</a> - A dynamic, any to any, pixel format translation library.</li>
<h2>Multimedia Processing</h2>
<li><a href="http://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/">GStreamer</a> - A powerful framework for creating multimedia applications.</li>
<h2>Templating</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/arteymix/compose">Compose</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/arteymix/compose" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">14</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":14,"repo":"arteymix/compose"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A functional templating library for Vala.</li>
<li><a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/template-glib">template-glib</a> - A library for template expansion which supports calling into GObject Introspection from templates.</li>
<h2>Crypto &#x26; Security</h2>
<li><a href="https://www.gnutls.org/">GnuTLS</a> - A secure communications library implementing the SSL, TLS and DTLS protocols and technologies around them. It provides a simple API to access the secure communications protocols as well as APIs to parse and write X.509, PKCS #12, and other required structures.</li>
<h2>Web Development</h2>
<li><a href="https://github.com/valum-framework/valum">Valum</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/valum-framework/valum" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">204</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":204,"repo":"valum-framework/valum"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Web micro-framework entirely written in Vala.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/AmbitionFramework/ambition">Ambition</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/AmbitionFramework/ambition" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">31</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":31,"repo":"AmbitionFramework/ambition"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A web framework written in Vala, with the MVC pattern in mind. Kinda unmaintained (someone could refactor it to use Valum under the hood, and maybe move it to Meson 😉)</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2018-48</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala/week/#2018-48</guid><pubDate>Mon, 26 Nov 2018 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>